1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:04,000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:01:49,960 --> 00:01:53,550
Marine Branch 153
Shells Town, East Blue

3
00:01:53,550 --> 00:01:54,800
"Cabin Boy"

4
00:02:02,100 --> 00:02:03,310
Hey! Quit slackin' off!

5
00:02:03,310 --> 00:02:04,150
Okay.

6
00:02:04,150 --> 00:02:06,810
Hey, cabin boys!
After sweeping, wash the windows!

7
00:02:06,810 --> 00:02:07,940
Yes, sir!

8
00:02:07,940 --> 00:02:16,240
– One! Two! Three! Four!
– One! Two! Three! Four!

9
00:02:07,980 --> 00:02:13,240
The Trials of Koby-Meppo

10
00:02:17,620 --> 00:02:22,710
I can't stand this. Forget Koby—
why do I have to be a cabin boy?!

11
00:02:25,540 --> 00:02:29,460
Dammit! I only ended up here
because of that Straw Hat!

12
00:02:32,050 --> 00:02:33,720
It's all his fault!

13
00:02:33,720 --> 00:02:38,050
It's all because of Straw Hat
that I'm stuck doing this crap!

14
00:02:38,050 --> 00:02:39,010
Helmeppo.

15
00:02:39,010 --> 00:02:41,520
What do you want?!
Don't act like we're friends!

16
00:02:41,520 --> 00:02:46,310
Nothing good comes from blaming Luffy
for everything that happens.

17
00:02:46,310 --> 00:02:50,820
For a long time, you lived protected
by your father's influence.

18
00:02:50,820 --> 00:02:55,200
But from now on, we need to
face forward and seek our own dreams!

19
00:02:55,200 --> 00:02:56,490
What are you...?

20
00:02:57,030 --> 00:02:58,950
I have a dream.

21
00:02:58,950 --> 00:03:03,910
Someday, I will be a Marine officer
who cracks down on bad guys!

22
00:03:07,290 --> 00:03:08,960
What are you going on about?!

23
00:03:08,960 --> 00:03:12,340
A wimp like you becoming
an officer for the Marines?!

24
00:03:12,340 --> 00:03:13,460
Quit dreaming!

25
00:03:13,460 --> 00:03:14,670
I will do it!

26
00:03:14,670 --> 00:03:17,640
I decided on it after seeing
how Luffy lives his life!

27
00:03:17,550 --> 00:03:20,510
I'm gonna be King of the Pirates!

28
00:03:20,510 --> 00:03:24,980
This is what I've decided,
so if I die, then fine by me!

29
00:03:25,600 --> 00:03:28,600
So just like Luffy, I've made up
my mind to risk everything

30
00:03:28,600 --> 00:03:29,940
and pursue a goal of my own!

31
00:03:30,940 --> 00:03:33,820
You see? So let's work hard together!

32
00:03:33,820 --> 00:03:34,690
Screw you!

33
00:03:34,690 --> 00:03:36,740
How dare you lecture me?!

34
00:03:36,740 --> 00:03:39,120
Just when did you get
so full of yourself?!

35
00:03:39,120 --> 00:03:43,120
What could you possibly learn
from that despicable Straw Hat?!

36
00:03:43,120 --> 00:03:45,250
Don't insult Luffy!

37
00:03:45,250 --> 00:03:47,290
I haven't said anything wrong!

38
00:03:47,290 --> 00:03:50,130
Wrong or not,
you still piss me off!

39
00:03:51,170 --> 00:03:54,170
Helmeppo! Please!
You have to be realistic.

40
00:03:54,170 --> 00:03:55,720
Look who's talking!

41
00:03:55,720 --> 00:03:56,670
Take this!

42
00:03:56,670 --> 00:03:58,800
Get ahold of yourself!

43
00:03:59,550 --> 00:04:00,640
Huh? What's going on?!

44
00:04:18,650 --> 00:04:21,910
– W-We're sorry!
– We're sorry!

45
00:04:24,320 --> 00:04:27,290
Really? The explosion earlier
was because of you?

46
00:04:27,790 --> 00:04:30,170
So then they kicked 
you out of the Marines?

47
00:04:30,170 --> 00:04:31,250
Thank you.

48
00:04:31,250 --> 00:04:34,250
No, we managed
to avoid being discharged.

49
00:04:35,880 --> 00:04:39,880
But now we're under
a fifty-year contract with no pay.

50
00:04:39,880 --> 00:04:42,550
Getting canned 
would've been a mercy.

51
00:04:43,470 --> 00:04:45,310
Attention!

52
00:04:47,020 --> 00:04:49,980
I will now fill you in
on our current mission!

53
00:04:52,520 --> 00:04:54,650
– Hey!
– What do you want?!

54
00:04:55,610 --> 00:04:58,070
D-Daddy...

55
00:04:58,530 --> 00:05:02,070
Morgan, a former Marine captain,
is to be sent to headquarters

56
00:05:02,070 --> 00:05:07,370
to face a court-martial for the crimes
of military exploitation and civilian torment!

57
00:05:07,370 --> 00:05:11,080
Today's mission is his transfer
and delivery to Vice Admiral Garp!

58
00:05:12,120 --> 00:05:14,960
I am Captain "Axe-Hand" Morgan
of the Marines!

59
00:05:14,960 --> 00:05:18,420
Scum without rank or status
should kneel before me!

60
00:05:32,060 --> 00:05:33,980
This was the only outcome, wasn't it?

61
00:05:35,060 --> 00:05:38,650
I'm not denying that he should be
court-martialed or whatever.

62
00:05:39,860 --> 00:05:42,360
He deserves what's coming
to him, after all.

63
00:05:43,160 --> 00:05:47,370
But even so, I used to respect him.

64
00:05:56,790 --> 00:05:57,920
Damn it!

65
00:05:59,050 --> 00:06:00,130
Why?!

66
00:06:03,260 --> 00:06:06,890
Tell me, do you think
they'll execute him?

67
00:06:06,890 --> 00:06:09,220
Th-That's...

68
00:06:10,020 --> 00:06:13,940
There's probably no getting 
around that either, huh?

69
00:06:15,190 --> 00:06:16,690
That's just how Daddy is.

70
00:06:22,320 --> 00:06:24,320
Helmeppo...

71
00:06:24,320 --> 00:06:27,160
All hands on deck!

72
00:06:27,660 --> 00:06:29,700
Fall in!

73
00:06:32,620 --> 00:06:35,830
– It's Vice Admiral Garp!
– It's Garp the Fist!

74
00:06:39,880 --> 00:06:43,840
So that's Marine Headquarters'
Vice Admiral Garp the Fist!

75
00:06:39,920 --> 00:06:43,840
Vice Admiral Garp
Marine Headquarters

76
00:06:44,630 --> 00:06:47,800
Traveling all over the Grand Line,
he's the hero of the seas!

77
00:06:55,390 --> 00:06:58,940
Vice Admiral Garp, thank you
for personally coming all this way!

78
00:06:56,060 --> 00:07:01,320
"Justice"

79
00:06:58,940 --> 00:07:01,320
We hereby deliver to you Morgan!

80
00:07:06,030 --> 00:07:08,530
Stop, Helmeppo!

81
00:07:06,860 --> 00:07:08,530
Umm... Vice Admiral Garp?

82
00:07:09,620 --> 00:07:11,240
Vice Admiral Garp!

83
00:07:11,240 --> 00:07:12,370
Quiet!

84
00:07:12,370 --> 00:07:14,410
I hear you.

85
00:07:14,410 --> 00:07:17,330
I've been up for five days now.

86
00:07:17,710 --> 00:07:19,630
Thank you for your hard work, sir!

87
00:07:19,630 --> 00:07:23,340
It's no big deal since I'm trying for
a new doughnut-eating record.

88
00:07:23,340 --> 00:07:24,340
Sir?

89
00:07:24,670 --> 00:07:30,890
But a lack of rest and sleep 
is getting to me after the 842nd one.

90
00:07:32,720 --> 00:07:34,680
Old man, cut the sleeping act.

91
00:07:43,070 --> 00:07:45,070
Everybody freeze!

92
00:07:47,610 --> 00:07:53,160
Move and I'll hack up this cabin boy
and feed him to the sharks!

93
00:07:53,160 --> 00:07:55,120
D-Daddy!

94
00:07:55,120 --> 00:07:56,750
Please stop!

95
00:07:56,750 --> 00:07:59,750
Helmeppo's your own son, isn't he?!

96
00:07:59,750 --> 00:08:02,210
Son?! I don't need such a thing!

97
00:08:02,710 --> 00:08:04,710
What I want is freedom!

98
00:08:04,710 --> 00:08:09,180
I'll smash him to
a bloody pulp if need be!

99
00:08:09,840 --> 00:08:12,140
D-Daddy...

100
00:08:13,220 --> 00:08:16,100
H-Help me!

101
00:08:16,100 --> 00:08:18,020
So long, suckers!

102
00:08:18,020 --> 00:08:19,770
Helmeppo!

103
00:08:19,770 --> 00:08:21,310
Ready the cannon!

104
00:08:21,940 --> 00:08:23,610
Load! Aim!

105
00:08:23,610 --> 00:08:26,150
Target: 16 degrees starboard.

106
00:08:26,150 --> 00:08:29,490
Distance: eight, two,
six, three. Ready!

107
00:08:29,820 --> 00:08:31,910
P-P-Please wait!

108
00:08:30,990 --> 00:08:31,910
That's dangerous!

109
00:08:31,910 --> 00:08:34,450
– What are you doing?!
– Get down from there!

110
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:38,460
P-Please don't shoot! My friend...

111
00:08:38,460 --> 00:08:40,620
My friend's onboard!

112
00:08:40,620 --> 00:08:41,790
Move.

113
00:08:42,330 --> 00:08:44,000
No!

114
00:08:44,500 --> 00:08:46,260
Then I'll cut you down!

115
00:08:48,550 --> 00:08:51,340
That's much better than
just abandoning my friend!

116
00:08:51,930 --> 00:08:54,850
Please! I'll go capture him myself!

117
00:09:07,610 --> 00:09:09,550
Come back, you idiot!

118
00:09:09,550 --> 00:09:11,740
There's no way you can capture him!

119
00:09:11,740 --> 00:09:13,070
Just let him go.

120
00:09:13,570 --> 00:09:16,040
He's either a complete lunatic, or...

121
00:09:19,500 --> 00:09:20,620
What do we do?!

122
00:09:28,090 --> 00:09:31,590
What's with all the racket?
I'm finally awake.

123
00:09:31,590 --> 00:09:34,430
Vice Admiral Garp,
we thought you were a goner!

124
00:09:34,430 --> 00:09:36,640
Huh?! Who's a goner?!

125
00:09:37,680 --> 00:09:41,020
I missed it because I was asleep!
Where's the victim?!

126
00:09:46,360 --> 00:09:47,440
Me?

127
00:09:51,990 --> 00:09:53,740
I'm free!

128
00:09:53,740 --> 00:09:56,830
Just you watch! The world
will kneel before me once again!

129
00:09:56,830 --> 00:10:00,700
Today, I begin a new life
as the ruler of the Morgan Kingdom!

130
00:10:00,700 --> 00:10:03,670
Now! Set our course west!

131
00:10:03,670 --> 00:10:06,210
What are you doing?!
I said to set course due west!

132
00:10:06,210 --> 00:10:07,170
No!

133
00:10:07,880 --> 00:10:09,710
I'll have no part in this!

134
00:10:09,710 --> 00:10:13,220
Despite what happened,
he still covered for us!

135
00:10:13,220 --> 00:10:16,180
Even when getting sacked
by the Marines would end his dream!

136
00:10:16,180 --> 00:10:19,640
After all that, he's still
protecting me! I can do it, too!

137
00:10:19,640 --> 00:10:22,730
I'm going to capture you, Dad!
Just give up–

138
00:10:25,980 --> 00:10:29,980
Are you dim?! Who do you think
you're talking to, huh?!

139
00:10:29,980 --> 00:10:32,820
What can useless scum
like you do to me?!

140
00:10:33,990 --> 00:10:35,030
Dammit!

141
00:10:35,030 --> 00:10:37,490
Know your place, you pathetic insect!

142
00:10:37,490 --> 00:10:40,160
As if I'd ever listen to you!

143
00:10:40,160 --> 00:10:43,210
I'm the one who decides how I'll live!

144
00:10:44,210 --> 00:10:47,710
Quit getting the wrong idea!
What can a piece of scum like you do?!

145
00:10:47,710 --> 00:10:49,840
He isn't alone!

146
00:10:51,670 --> 00:10:52,510
You!

147
00:10:53,590 --> 00:10:54,880
Morgan!

148
00:11:01,680 --> 00:11:04,810
Pathetic! Pathetic! Pathetic!

149
00:11:04,810 --> 00:11:07,980
So what if a couple of insects
are swarming together?!

150
00:11:07,980 --> 00:11:11,030
Get in my way, and I'll
end you both in one fell swoop!

151
00:11:11,030 --> 00:11:14,110
I'm sorry you got dragged into this
when you tried to save me.

152
00:11:14,490 --> 00:11:16,070
What are you talking about?

153
00:11:16,070 --> 00:11:17,570
Aren't we friends?

154
00:11:18,820 --> 00:11:20,160
Koby...

155
00:11:25,120 --> 00:11:27,790
You damn insects
aren't even worth killing.

156
00:11:27,790 --> 00:11:30,210
Never show yourselves to me again!

157
00:11:31,130 --> 00:11:32,630
Morgan!

158
00:11:33,010 --> 00:11:35,260
I'll let you go for today,

159
00:11:35,880 --> 00:11:38,930
but someday I will surpass you!

160
00:11:39,760 --> 00:11:42,390
Someday, I will catch you!

161
00:11:42,390 --> 00:11:44,060
Just you wait!

162
00:11:47,900 --> 00:11:50,150
Please forgive my poor supervision!

163
00:11:50,150 --> 00:11:52,940
Letting him flee is
the biggest blunder in my life!

164
00:11:52,940 --> 00:11:55,030
We're very sorry, sir!

165
00:11:55,030 --> 00:11:57,990
These two are now forever
barred from military service!

166
00:12:01,080 --> 00:12:03,330
You two truly are lost causes.

167
00:12:03,330 --> 00:12:06,000
I doubt anyone anywhere
would take you in now.

168
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:08,540
And if we turn you loose,
you'd be a nuisance to all.

169
00:12:08,540 --> 00:12:11,670
You leave me no choice.
Come with me to Marine Headquarters!

170
00:12:13,250 --> 00:12:17,050
Vice Admiral! You're taking them
with you to Marine Headquarters?!

171
00:12:17,050 --> 00:12:18,050
Am I not allowed?

172
00:12:18,680 --> 00:12:20,510
No, do as you please.

173
00:12:21,300 --> 00:12:22,760
Any objections, you two?

174
00:12:23,180 --> 00:12:25,270
If you want to run away,
now's your chance.

175
00:12:25,720 --> 00:12:29,230
Though I have no intention
of letting you say no.

176
00:12:29,230 --> 00:12:32,560
My, oh my, what an odd day
this has been!

177
00:12:49,460 --> 00:12:52,460
What?! Marine Headquarters?!

178
00:12:52,840 --> 00:12:56,800
Yeah. Vice Admiral Garp seems
to be as eccentric as people say.

179
00:12:57,510 --> 00:13:00,090
But doesn't he have
an exceptional reputation?

180
00:13:00,090 --> 00:13:01,970
Yeah, you have no idea.

181
00:13:02,340 --> 00:13:06,060
Then those two must show 
a lot of promise.

182
00:13:06,640 --> 00:13:07,390
Hm?

183
00:13:11,480 --> 00:13:14,690
Stupid! Stupid! Stupid! Stupid! Stupid!
Stupid! Stupid! Stupid! Stupid! Stupid!

184
00:13:14,690 --> 00:13:17,400
Why did you let them go
without saying anything?!

185
00:13:17,400 --> 00:13:19,820
Stupid! Stupid!
Stupid! Stupid! Stupid!

186
00:13:19,820 --> 00:13:23,120
I... wanted to play with them more.

187
00:13:23,950 --> 00:13:26,910
I wanted to talk to them more.

188
00:13:27,410 --> 00:13:34,080
I was learning how to cook so I could
make them tasty lunch boxes!

189
00:13:35,090 --> 00:13:39,300
I didn't even get to say goodbye!

190
00:13:40,670 --> 00:13:41,680
Ah... Um...

191
00:13:41,680 --> 00:13:43,760
Why did they leave?!

192
00:13:43,760 --> 00:13:46,680
Ah, I'm sorry! Forgive me!

193
00:13:46,680 --> 00:13:49,770
Rika, that's enough. Leave him alone.

194
00:13:49,770 --> 00:13:55,020
Don't worry. They'll surely be back...
once they become fine officers.

195
00:14:00,150 --> 00:14:02,320
"The Marines"

196
00:14:00,940 --> 00:14:02,320
But at any rate,

197
00:14:02,360 --> 00:14:07,910
Marine Headquarters

198
00:14:02,780 --> 00:14:06,450
can we really become Marines
by doing things like this?

199
00:14:06,450 --> 00:14:08,870
This might be that
old dog's hobby, you know.

200
00:14:08,870 --> 00:14:09,870
Hobby?

201
00:14:10,500 --> 00:14:14,630
Yup. It's called "the retired geezer's
torment of youths."

202
00:14:14,630 --> 00:14:18,130
Don't you think he's shifty
and strange enough for that?

203
00:14:18,130 --> 00:14:19,300
Shut up, birds!
